description: Chief Justice D.Y. Chandrachud has successfully reduced the Supreme Court's backlog by 10,000 cases during his tenure.  His approach emphasized transparency by publicly disclosing pending case details and prioritizing bail cases for expedited resolution. Despite a significant influx of new cases, Chandrachud's strategies led to the disposal of over 100,000 cases.
title: Pendency in SC came down by 10,000 cases in last 2 years: CJI

description: In his final act as Chief Justice of India, D.Y. Chandrachud heard a petition advocating for the inclusion of traditional Indian healthcare practices, such as Ayurveda and Yoga, into the national health insurance program, PM-JAY. While dismissing a previous petition by the same advocate, the court acknowledged the importance of integrating these systems into mainstream healthcare.
title: Hearing last PIL, CJI bats for inclusion of Indian healthcare system in PM-JAY

description: The Supreme Court of India has urged government bodies to shift their focus from the disabilities of individuals to their abilities. The court emphasized that denying reasonable accommodations to differently-abled individuals constitutes discrimination and violates their fundamental rights. This statement came as the court granted the plea of a medical aspirant denied admission to an MBBS program due to an inaccurate disability assessment.
title: Barring disabled a sign of bias, violates their rights, says SC

description: The UK government is navigating a diplomatic challenge as past criticisms of US President-elect Donald Trump by Labour Party members resurface. Trump's lawyers have called for an investigation into potential foreign interference related to Labour staff campaigning for Kamala Harris. Despite previous strong criticisms, Labour figures, including Keir Starmer and David Lammy, have reached out to Trump and emphasized the importance of the US-UK relationship.
title: After Labour attack on Don, UK scrambles to mend US ties

description: A CRPF constable, Shailendra Rajput, has been arrested for the kidnapping and murder of his neighbor's eight-year-old son in Ankleshwar, Gujarat. Driven by a debt of Rs 16 lakh incurred from stock market losses, Rajput kidnapped the child and demanded a ransom of Rs 5 lakh.
title: Debt-hit CRPF jawan abducts kid for ransom, kills him in Gujarat

description: The Supreme Court advised high courts to exercise caution when ordering medical colleges to reserve seats for students alleging unfair admission denials. The court emphasized that such orders should only be issued in exceptional cases with strong evidence, as vacant seats result in significant financial losses for colleges.
title: SC ticks off courts for blocking MBBS seats

description: A Bengaluru couple, Sagar Gurung and Urmila Kumari, were arrested for growing ganja in their home garden. Their secret hobby came to light after Urmila posted a video of their plants on social media, where netizens identified the illegal saplings.  Police raided their home and found the discarded plants, leading to their arrest under the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act.
title: Reel slip-up lands couple in soup over balcony ganja cultivation

description: The National Medical Commission (NMC) has set a final deadline of November 23 for all medical colleges in India to submit detailed information on their MBBS admissions for the 2024-25 academic year. This measure aims to ensure admissions adhere to merit-based guidelines and stay within the approved intake capacity, following instances of irregularities discovered in the previous year.
title: To rule out irregularities, NMC asks med colleges to submit details of admissions

description: Darul Uloom Deoband, a prominent Islamic seminary, has lifted its six-month ban on women entering its premises. The decision comes after concerns that women were disrupting students by filming social media content. Women are now allowed entry with male guardians, subject to providing personal information and adhering to a dress code. Photography and videography remain prohibited.
title: After 6-month ban, Darul opens doors to women, with riders

description: A parliamentary panel is set to discuss the possibility of extending caste-based reservations to the private sector in India. The proposal, a contentious issue with significant political and economic implications, aims to address concerns about shrinking opportunities for Dalits and tribals in the face of rapid privatization.
title: Parliament panel to debate proposal on private sector quota for Dalits, tribals

description: Two hospital staff members in Balrampur district, Chhattisgarh, have been suspended after allegedly forcing a woman's family to clean up after her delivery. The incident occurred on November 5th at Wadrafnagar Civil Hospital. The woman was reportedly in critical condition after the delivery. An investigation is underway, and officials say anyone found guilty will be punished.
title: Family forced to clean up after delivery at hospital, 2 suspended

description: Elon Musk's Starlink and Jeff Bezos's Amazon are facing delays in launching their satellite communication services in India. The Department of Telecommunications has imposed strict security requirements, demanding detailed compliance information on data security and coverage. While Indian companies have already received approval, the US giants' applications are pending, awaiting their response to the security stipulations.
title: Govt to Amazon & Starlink: Your satellite application can be processed only after ...

description: Elon Musk finds India's potential allocation of satellite broadband spectrum without auctions 'promising.' This comes amidst a heated debate between Indian telecom giants like Jio and Airtel, advocating for auctions, and global satellite players like Starlink and Amazon.
title: This is what Musk said on telecom minister Scindia's satellite broadband comment

description: A 75-year-old woman in Madhya Pradesh, India, was murdered for her silver anklets.  Her attackers hacked off her legs and left her in a drain to die. This horrific crime echoes similar incidents in the region, highlighting a disturbing pattern of violence targeting women for their jewelry.
title: Robbers hack off woman’s feet for her anklets, she bleeds to death

description: The Shiv Sena (UBT) and MNS are seeking permission from the BMC to hold their final assembly election rallies at Shivaji Park on November 17th.  The park, a coveted location for political events, has already hosted rallies by the Shiv Sena, BJP, and NCP. The BMC is awaiting a decision from the state government and Election Commission before granting permission.
title: Thackeray cousins vie for Shivaji Park to host Sunday rally

description: A minor student in Kanpur, preparing for NEET, was allegedly held hostage and raped by two of her teachers, Sahil Siddiqui and Vikas Porwal, for over six months. Siddiqui allegedly filmed the assault and used it to blackmail her. The survivor filed a complaint a year later after seeing a video of Siddiqui harassing another student. Both teachers have been arrested.
title: Minor NEET aspirant held hostage, raped for over six months in Kanpur

description: During a college anniversary event in Rewa, BJP MP Janardan Mishra delivered an unusual speech expressing concerns about technology's impact on human relationships. He pondered the future of marriage, childbirth, and human interaction in an increasingly digital world, leaving attendees surprised.
title: BJP MP stuns audience with his ‘babies being born online’ remark

description: Hindu seers in Prayagraj have criticized Samajwadi Party leader Dimple Yadav for condemning the Akhil Bharatiya Akhara Parishad's proposal to bar non-Hindus from participating in the Maha Kumbh.  The seers defended the proposal, arguing that it would protect Hindu traditions and practices.
title: Dimple Yadav opposes Kumbh shop rider, draws ire of seers

description: Five Election Commission officials in Ulhasnagar are facing bribery charges after allegedly extorting Rs 75,000 from a flower trader carrying Rs 7.5 lakh with proper documentation. Despite the officials returning the bribe money, claiming a mistake, a senior official confirmed a crime was committed and proper video recording protocols were not followed.
title: 5 EC officials ‘extort’ Rs75,000 from trader, bribery FIR filed

description: As Mumbai gears up for elections, candidates are leveraging social media, particularly hashtags, to connect with voters and highlight their campaigns. While some believe these online strategies can influence voters, others view them as mere propaganda, emphasizing that voters prioritize tangible solutions over catchy slogans.
title: Battle of buzzwords: Netas turn to hashtags for edge

description: The BJP has criticized the Congress and its allies in the Maha Vikas Aghadi (MVA) over a list of 17 demands presented by the All India Ulema Board. The demands, which include 10% job reservations for Muslims, have sparked accusations of appeasement politics and attempts to divide society along religious lines.
title: Amit Shah attacks Congress for ‘promising help’ to Muslims to get 10% quota

description: While campaigning in Aligarh, Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath advocated for extending reservation benefits to SC/ST/OBC communities at Aligarh Muslim University. He criticized opposition parties for allegedly neglecting the rights of these communities and hindering reservation implementation at AMU for political gains.
title: Yogi calls for SC/ST, OBC quota in AMU

description: Three coaches of the Secunderabad-Shalimar Weekly Express derailed near Kolkata, causing significant delays but no injuries. Over 1,200 passengers were safely evacuated, and train services resumed after a 12-hour disruption. An investigation is underway, with officials suspecting a possible error in the railway track points.
title: Close shave for 1,200 as 3 coaches of train derail near Kolkata

description: A tiger was found dead in Chhattisgarh's Guru Ghasidas National Park, likely due to poisoning. This is the second such incident in two years, raising concerns about poaching in the area. The park's designation as a tiger reserve is pending, and activists are urging for stricter measures to protect wildlife.
title: Alarm bells over Chhattisgarh tiger death

description: Mira Road police have filed a case against five individuals and social media accounts for spreading false information linking Congress candidate Muzaffar Hussain to terrorist groups. The fabricated documents, circulated online, falsely claimed Hussain's support for a mercy plea of a 1993 blasts convict.  The accused face charges for inciting religious disharmony and violating electoral laws.
title: FIR on five for linking Congress nominee to 1993 case convict

description: Avian botulism, a bacterial illness, has been identified as the cause of recent bird deaths at Sambhar Lake in India.  Over 600 birds have died since October 26th, primarily scavenger species.  Rescue teams are working to prevent the spread of the disease and treat affected birds, while thousands of migratory birds continue to arrive at the lake.
title: Avian botulism kills 600 migratory birds at Sambhar

description: At a series of rallies in Maharashtra, NCP (SCP) chief Sharad Pawar accused the BJP of fostering communal division and criticized Dhananjay Munde for splitting the NCP. Pawar urged voters to reject divisive politics and highlighted the plight of farmers and unemployed youth under the current government.
title: Netas like Yogi Adityanath brought in to sow discord: Sharad Pawar

description: A road sign in Raipur, India, directing people to 'RSS University' instead of the correctly abbreviated 'PRSU' for Pt. Ravishankar Shukla University has sparked controversy.  Congress members see it as a politically motivated move by the ruling party and plan to file complaints with the government and university administration. They emphasize the need to uphold the legacy of Pt. Shukla, the first Chief Minister of undivided Madhya Pradesh.
title: Political row brews over road sign to Raipur’s ‘RSS university’

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during rallies in Maharashtra, accused Congress of promoting Pakistan's agenda by seeking the reinstatement of Article 370 in Jammu and Kashmir. He criticized Congress for allegedly turning states under its rule into "ATMs" for personal gain and urged voters to choose BJP for progress and cultural pride.
title: Congress turning states governed by it into ATMs for its ‘royal family’: PM Modi

description: Maharashtra's political parties are leveraging technology to engage voters in the upcoming election. While NCP utilizes AI for personalized messages and captivating videos, BJP focuses on podcasts and interactive tap cards for manifesto contributions. Shiv Sena (UBT) employs podcasts and AI-powered video messages, emphasizing a direct connection with voters.
title: AI lends a new tech touch to campaigns this assembly poll

description: Within two days, two women were murdered in separate incidents in Manipur, India.  On Saturday, suspected militants shot and killed a 27-year-old woman while she was farming in Bishnupur district. This follows the Thursday night murder of a 31-year-old woman who was allegedly assaulted and burned to death in Jiribam district. Police are investigating both incidents.
title: Manipur women working in fields fired upon, 1 killed

description: Congress government in Karnataka has accused the former BJP government of financial mismanagement during the COVID-19 pandemic. A preliminary report by the Justice Michael D'Cunha Commission of Inquiry allegedly found that the BJP government misspent funds on medical supplies and recommended the prosecution of former Chief Minister Yediyurappa and former Health Minister Sriramulu. The BJP has denied the allegations, calling them politically motivated.
title: Congress leaks probe report to attack BSY ahead of bypoll

description: Indian security agencies are concerned about a surge in social media activity from Pakistan-linked terrorist groups, aiming to recruit young people in Jammu and Kashmir. This online push coincides with a sharp decline in local terrorist recruitment, suggesting a strategy shift by these groups.  The increase in online activity is being linked to the recent establishment of an elected government in the region.
title: Pakistan on social media overdrive to revive terrorism in Kashmir

description: Three members of a family in Bhagalpur district, India, tragically lost their lives due to asphyxiation inside a septic tank. Punit Yadav slipped into the tank while trying to retrieve a tool, and his wife and a relative also fell in while attempting a rescue. All three succumbed to the toxic fumes before help could arrive.
title: Couple among 3 die due to asphyxiation in septic tank

description: A terrorist was killed in an ongoing anti-terror operation in Rampora, Sopore, by security forces.  This is the second encounter in the area in 24 hours and the fourth in North Kashmir in five days.  The operation began based on intelligence inputs about the presence of two to three terrorists.  While sources suggest the slain terrorist was Pakistani, official confirmation is awaited.
title: Terrorist killed in Sopore gun battle; operation underway

description: Telangana Chief Minister Revanth Reddy defended his government's acceptance of a ₹100 crore donation from the Adani Group for a skills university.  Reddy, alongside other Congress leaders, highlighted their states' welfare schemes, countering BJP's criticism of Congress's poll guarantees. They argued that if the BJP could write off large corporate loans, Congress-led states could implement pro-poor initiatives.
title: Revanth Reddy differs with Rahul Gandhi, says it's OK to take Adani funds

description: Two village defense guards, Nazir Ahmed and Kuldeep Kumar, were found dead in a forest in Kishtwar district, Jammu, after being abducted and killed by suspected Jaish-e-Mohammed terrorists. The unarmed men were grazing cattle when they were taken. Their deaths sparked outrage and calls for increased security measures from villagers.
title: Amid anti-Pak slogans, farewell to slain VDGs in J&K’s Kishtwar

description: UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer's Diwali celebration at No. 10 Downing Street sparked controversy among British Indians. The inclusion of meat and alcohol in the menu drew criticism and was deemed disrespectful to the religious significance of the festival. Hindu groups expressed disappointment and urged for cultural sensitivity in future events.
title: No 10 Diwali party serves alcohol and meat, leaves British Indians repulsed

description: Kamala Harris' presidential campaign invested heavily in media appearances, including a $1 million payment to Oprah Winfrey for a rally and interview. Despite significant spending on events and podcasts, some critics argue these efforts failed to resonate with voters or distance Harris from the then-current administration.
title: Oprah reportedly charged $1 million for hosting Harris' interview and campaign

description: During his Jharkhand campaign trail, Rahul Gandhi criticized the Modi government for record inflation and unemployment, attributing it to divisive politics. He highlighted the INDIA bloc's initiatives in the state, including direct cash transfers and a health insurance scheme. Gandhi assured tribal communities of their rightful recognition and promised a caste census and removal of the 50% reservation cap if INDIA is voted to power.
title: Politics of hate, violence, anger behind crashing economy: Rahul Gandhi
Biden, Trump to meet at White House on Wednesday
No tribal rights to children of Bangladeshi infiltrator: Nadda in Jharkhand
How US president-elect Trump plans to end Russia-Ukraine war

description: A leaked image of Prabhas from the upcoming Telugu film 'Kannappa' has prompted the production house, 24 Frames Factory, to offer a Rs 5 lakh reward for information leading to the source of the leak. The team expressed disappointment over the unauthorized release, emphasizing the years of hard work invested in the project.
title: Prabhas’ leaked photo from upcoming movie 'Kannappa' viral on social media

description: Pakistan's Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif faced criticism for congratulating Donald Trump on X, formerly Twitter, despite a ban on the platform in Pakistan. A community note highlighted Sharif's alleged use of a VPN to bypass the ban, which the government imposed citing national security concerns and misuse of the platform.
title: Why Pak PM's congratulatory message to Trump was 'flagged' as 'unlawful'

description: Dhruv Jurel impressed in the second unofficial Test against Australia A with scores of 80 and 68, showcasing his resilience despite India A's loss.  Jurel, who averages over 63 in Test matches, is eager to learn and contribute in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar series starting November 22nd.
title: 'Batting on Aussie soil ... ': Dhruv Jurel

description: Qatar has withdrawn from its role as a mediator in Gaza ceasefire negotiations and plans to expel Hamas leaders from Doha. The decision comes after unsuccessful attempts to broker a truce between Hamas and Israel, with Qatar citing a lack of "good faith" negotiations.
title: 'Serves no purpose': Qatar out of Gaza truce talks, to expel Hamas leaders

description: NFL legend Tom Brady considers a heartfelt embrace with his son, Jack, after the 2021 NFC Championship game as his most treasured football memory. This touching moment, where Brady asked security to greet his son, eclipsed even his Super Bowl victories. Brady, a father of three, has always emphasized the importance of family.
title: The seven-time Super Bowl winner Tom Brady recalls emotional moment

description: Iran has denied US allegations of an assassination plot against former President Donald Trump. The US Justice Department alleges an Iranian official directed a plan involving surveillance and assassination of Trump in October 2024. The plot also targeted journalist Masih Alinejad. Three men face charges including murder-for-hire and conspiracy.
title: 'Baseless': Iran denies involvement in Trump assassination plot
Encounter breaks out between security forces and terrorists in J&K's Baramulla

description: A 17-year-old student in Kanpur endured months of horrific abuse after being lured to a fake New Year's party by her coaching teacher, Sahil Siddiqui. Siddiqui drugged and raped her, capturing the assault on video, and held her captive for six months, subjecting her to repeated assaults. Another teacher, Vikas Porwal, also participated in the abuse.
title: Neet aspirant's 6-month trauma: Minor held hostage, raped by two teachers in Kanpur

description: Pakistan cricket legend Rashid Latif and PCB Chairman Mohsin Naqvi have expressed strong reactions to the reports suggesting India might not travel to Pakistan for the 2025 Champions Trophy due to security concerns. They emphasized the ICC's binding tournament commitments and highlighted the recent successful tours of other major cricketing nations to Pakistan.
title: 'India can't simply deny participation': Ex-Pak sends strong message

description: Virat Kohli's recent form slump has cast a shadow over India's upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy campaign against Australia. Despite a stellar career record against the Aussies, Kohli's dwindling Test average and lack of centuries in recent years have raised concerns. However, former Australian captain Ricky Ponting remains optimistic about Kohli's ability to turn things around on Australian soil.
title: 'Do not ever question the greats': Ponting on Kohli's lean patch

description: Yashvardhan Dalal from Haryana created a new tournament record in the Col. CK Nayudu Trophy by smashing an unbeaten 426 runs against Mumbai. His innings, which included 58 boundaries, helped Haryana reach a commanding total of 732/8 at the end of Day 2.  Despite Ranga's dismissal for 151 by Atharva Bhosale, Dalal continued his aggressive approach, contributing significantly to Haryana's imposing total of 732 for eight wickets at the close of play on Day 2.
title: Haryana batsman slams 426 runs in an innings, becomes ...

description: Rahul Gandhi announced that a caste census has begun in Telangana and will soon follow in Maharashtra. He emphasized that this data will inform policies for inclusive development and challenged Prime Minister Modi's stance against a nationwide caste census.  Congress aims to surpass the 50% reservation limit based on the census findings.
title: 'In Maharashtra soon': Rahul Gandhi's caste census challenge to PM Modi

description: Chief Justice of India (CJI) DY Chandrachud marked his final working day at the Supreme Court on Friday, concluding his tenure that began in 2016.  During his time as a Supreme Court judge, he authored 613 judgments, including landmark rulings on privacy, same-sex relationships, adultery, and the Sabarimala temple entry.
title: As CJI Chandrachud bids adieu to SC, a look at his top 10 judgements

description: National Conference MLA Qaiser Jamshaid Lone revealed in the Jammu and Kashmir Legislative Assembly that he contemplated joining militancy as a teenager after experiencing torture from an army officer. His faith was restored after a senior officer intervened and reprimanded the junior officer.
title: J&K MLA says he wanted to be militant after 'torture' by army officer

description: Canadian authorities are increasing security measures at the US border, anticipating a potential surge in migrants due to President-elect Donald Trump's strict immigration policies.  The RCMP is deploying more resources and collaborating with US officials to monitor the situation, while the Canadian government assures preparedness for potential challenges.
title: Canada on 'high alert', braces for potential migrant surge from US after Trump’s return

description: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath addressed rallies in Mainpuri, Azamgarh, and Kanpur, emphasizing unity and development. He also inaugurated the Gomti Book Festival in Lucknow, encouraging youth to read and cautioning against excessive technology use. Adityanath highlighted India's traditional knowledge systems and the importance of productive time management.
title: Yogi’s supporters attend rally in Mainpuri on bulldozers -Watch

description: Indian Paralympian Navdeep Singh recently appeared on The Great Indian Kapil Show. He shared a funny moment with actor Rajpal Yadav. The interaction went viral on social media. Navdeep won a gold medal at the Paris 2024 Paralympics. He set a season-best throw in the men's javelin F41 event. India achieved a record-breaking performance at the Paralympics.
title: Fans can’t stop laughing at Navdeep and Rajpal's epic exchange
'Yogi ji's or Modi ji's?': Kharge asks BJP to decide on its slogan

description: India's Finance Minister, Nirmala Sitharaman, refuted claims that patriarchy hinders women's progress, citing Indira Gandhi's prime ministership as evidence. She highlighted government initiatives like internships for youth and support for MSMEs and digital banking. Sitharaman emphasized the government's role in fostering innovation and supporting startups, leading to a thriving startup ecosystem.
title: In reply to question on patriarchy, Sitharaman cites Indira Gandhi's example

description: Sanju Samson's explosive century (107 off 50 balls) powered India to a commanding 61-run victory against South Africa in the first T20I in Durban. Samson credited captain Suryakumar Yadav and coach Gautam Gambhir for their unwavering support during his challenging phases. Their guidance and communication boosted his confidence, enabling him to deliver a match-winning performance.
title: Gambhir, Surya's 'phone calls': Sanju reveals story

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during a rally in Akola, accused Congress governments in Telangana, Karnataka, and Tamil Nadu of corruption, claiming they siphoned off Rs 700 crore. He contrasted this with his government's focus on development, citing the Vadhavan Port project and welfare schemes. Modi urged Maharashtra to reject "scam-prone" parties and support the BJP for continued progress.
title: PM Modi launches sharp critique on Congress' 'royal family'

description: Filmmaker Rohit Shetty steps in for Salman Khan on Bigg Boss 18's Weekend Ka Vaar, confronting Karan Veer Mehra for his passive stance in house conflicts. Shetty also criticizes Sara Arfeen Khan for her controversial remarks during an argument, questioning her behavior after she left her children to participate in the show.
title: Bigg Boss 18 promo: Rohit Shetty school Karan Veer Mehra

description: Congress Chief Ministers from Telangana and Himachal Pradesh, joined by Karnataka's Deputy CM, defended their states' performance against BJP criticism. They highlighted job creation, farmer-centric policies, and welfare schemes as successes, accusing the BJP of copying their initiatives and employing destabilizing tactics.
title: 'We prioritise development, not votes': Congress CMs hit back at BJP

description: Pakistani cricketer Ahmad Shahzad lauded Sanju Samson's consecutive T20I centuries, urging India to give him the recognition he deserves.  Shahzad emphasized the rarity of such a feat, highlighting Samson's back-to-back centuries against South Africa. Samson's blistering 107 off 50 balls in the first T20I powered India to a commanding victory, solidifying his place among T20 stalwarts.
title: 'Kyun hila dala na': Pak cricketer says Samson deserves respect

description: India triumphed over South Africa by 61 runs in the first T20I in Durban, taking a 1-0 lead in the series. Suryakumar Yadav spearheaded India's victory.  Indian bowlers Arshdeep Singh and Hardik Pandya are nearing Jasprit Bumrah's record of 89 T20I wickets. Both Pandya and Arshdeep played vital roles in India’s 2024 T20 World Cup triumph.
title: Hardik, Arshdeep inch closer to surpassing Bumrah

description: In his book 'Save America,' Donald Trump threatened legal action against Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg and Google, alleging election interference. Trump accused Meta of suppressing information and Google of promoting negative stories about him.
title: When Donald Trump threatened to jail Facebook founder Zuckerberg

description: Amit Shah, at a Jharkhand rally, cautioned Rahul Gandhi against promising Muslim reservations, stating it contradicts the Indian Constitution and would impact existing quotas for Dalits and tribals. He criticized Congress's historical stance on OBC reservations and contrasted it with PM Modi's initiatives. Shah also targeted the JMM-Congress-RJD alliance, citing corruption allegations.
title: 'Till BJP is present, minorities ...': Amit Shah warns Rahul over Muslim reservation

description: Canada has ended its Student Direct Stream (SDS) program, impacting students from India and 13 other countries. The program offered expedited study permit processing. The government aims to provide equal opportunities for all students by eliminating nationality-based fast-track options. Future applicants will now undergo the regular study permit application process.
title: Big blow for Indian students as Canada ends fast-track SDS visa scheme

description: The BJP's youth wing in Himachal Pradesh organized a 'Samosa March' to satirize the controversy surrounding an alleged investigation into snacks meant for CM Sukhvinder Singh Sukhu being mistakenly served to his security personnel.
title: 'Sukhu ji ka samosa kisne khaya?': Himachal politics spices up as CID probe missing snack

description: A 25-year-old man in Ahmedabad was hospitalized with multiple fractures and head injuries after a brutal attack by his girlfriend's father. The accused, vehemently opposed to their inter-caste relationship, allegedly rammed his car into the victim before assaulting him with a metal rod. Police have booked the assailant based on the victim's complaint.
title: Ahmedabad man rams car into daughter’s lover, beats him

description: Indian television actor Nitin Chauhaan was found dead in his Mumbai apartment on November 6. Police confirmed his death as suicide. Chauhaan was known for his roles in popular shows like Crime Patrol and Splitsvilla. He was found hanging from the ceiling fan by his wife.
title: Tera Yaar Hoon Main actor Nitin Chauhaan found dead at home; suicide confirmed

description: Donald Trump's 2024 US election victory sparked a surge in Americans searching for "How to move to Canada." Google Trends data revealed a 400% spike in these searches, particularly from states that favoured Kamala Harris.
title: Google Searches for 'move to Canada' have increased in US, here's the reason

description: A couple in Himachal Pradesh tied the knot through a video call due to the groom's inability to secure leave from his company in Turkiye.
title: 'Qubool Hai, Qubool Hai, Qubool Hai': From Turkiye to HP on video call

description: Umair Ashrafi, a Madrassa teacher from Kerala, was apprehended by police in Tanur after a student accused him of shocking abuse. Ashrafi allegedly branded the student with a hot iron and applied chili powder to the boy's sensitive areas as punishment for disobedience. After the allegations surfaced, Ashrafi fled the state, prompting a police search.
title: 'Applied chili on private parts': Madrassa teacher brands student with iron box

description: During a rally in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, BJP MLA Prashant Bamb's supporters allegedly removed a man for questioning Bamb's past campaign promises. A video circulating on social media shows the man being escorted out after Bamb tells him, "You will regret till your death..." Bamb claims the man was a plant by his opponent, Satish Chavan, attempting to disrupt his speech.
title: BJP MLA asks supporters to push man out of rally for asking questions

description: The Mumbai Crime Branch uncovered a plot by the Lawrence Bishnoi gang to assassinate a prominent political figure in Pune following their successful operation against Baba Siddique. Investigations revealed that the gang had a backup plan in place, involving shooters who had undergone weapons training in Jharkhand.
title: 'Plan B': Lawrence Bishnoi gang planned to kill Pune leader if Siddique attempt failed

description: Shiv Sena (UBT) leader Sanjay Raut countered Prime Minister Narendra Modi's call for unity, stating that Maharashtra seeks greater safety and aims to oust the BJP.  This follows controversy over pronouncements on Hindu unity and alleged caste-based politics surrounding the upcoming Maharashtra Assembly elections.
title: 'Batenge toh katenge' did not work: Sanjay Raut after PM Modi's 'ek hain ... ' remark

description: Chief Minister Eknath Shinde targeted Uddhav Thackeray's claim over Shiv Sena and its symbol. Shinde accused Thackeray of abandoning the party's principles. He highlighted his government's commitment to social welfare and growth. Shinde outlined plans for women's allowances, farmer loan waivers, and electricity bill relief.
title: Shiv Sena UBT's 'torch' not for revolution, but for burning people's homes: Shinde

description: Zoho CEO Sridhar Vembu criticised Freshworks' decision to lay off 12%-13% of its workforce, calling it "naked greed."
title: What Zoho CEO called '...to add insult to injury...' on Freshworks job cuts

description: Donald Trump announced a plan to restore freedom of expression. He pledged to eliminate the "left-wing censorship regime". He proposed a five-point strategy. It includes prohibiting federal bodies from partnering with private organizations on speech restriction. It also includes directing the Department of Justice to examine censorship activities. Trump will issue an executive order immediately after taking office.
title: Trump's five-point strategy after becoming President

description: Junior doctors in Kolkata will hold protests on Saturday to demand justice for 'Abhaya'. The protests will mark three months since the RG Kar rape-murder. A citizens' march will be held from College Square to Esplanade. A Gallery of Rebellion will be organised on medical college campuses. A public charge-sheet will be presented at Rani Rashmoni Avenue.
title: 3 months since RG Kar horror, junior doctors' to protest today in Kolkata

description: Former Indian cricketer Aakash Chopra has questioned Team India's decision to consistently place Rinku Singh lower down the batting order. Chopra believes that Rinku Singh, who has a proven track record of scoring runs at a brisk pace, should be given the opportunity to bat higher, ideally at number four.
title: 'Are we being fair to Rinku?': Ex-cricketer questions team's strategy

description: Josiah Medler, a young boy from Illinois, is a huge fan of Travis Kelce. Josiah's love for Kelce led him to become a fan of Taylor Swift. For his sixth birthday, Josiah received tickets to a Taylor Swift concert.  In 2023, a video of Josiah went viral, leading to him receiving tickets to a Chiefs game.
title: Young Travis Kelce fan receives heartwarming surprise from Taylor Swift

description: At the UN, India condemned Pakistan for attempting to derail discussions on peacekeeping by raising the issue of Jammu and Kashmir. Indian representative Sudhanshu Trivedi reiterated India's stance on Kashmir as an integral part of the nation, highlighting recent elections as proof of its democratic process.
title: 'J&K is, was and will remain India's integral part': Sudhanshu Trivedi slams Pak at UN

description: Pakistan's Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif congratulated Donald Trump on winning a second term as US President in a tweet, despite having banned X in Pakistan. X users pointed out the irony, noting that Sharif was using a VPN to access the platform illegally.
title: Community note on Pak PM Sharif's post claims 'unlawful VPN use'

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi extended his greetings to the people of Uttarakhand on their 25th State Foundation Day, emphasizing the central government's commitment to the state's development. He highlighted Uttarakhand's economic growth and urged tourists to prioritize cleanliness and responsible tourism. Chief Minister Pushkar Singh Dhami also marked the occasion, presenting Uttarakhand Ratna Awards to five individuals for their contributions.
title: PM extends wishes on U'khand foundation day, hails state's UCC stance

description: Devotees in New Delhi celebrated Chhath Puja in the Yamuna River despite its heavy pollution and a court order prohibiting it.  The Delhi High Court had deemed the river too polluted for the ritualistic bathing, citing health risks.  Videos circulating online show people submerged in the toxic foam covering the river, raising concerns about the potential health consequences.
title: Woman washes hair with toxic foam in Delhi's Yamuna, video goes viral

description: Multan, Pakistan, issued a high alert as the Air Quality Index (AQI) soared past 2,000, reaching hazardous levels. Schools and public spaces temporarily closed due to the dangerous smog.  The primary pollutant, PM2.5, reached alarming levels, prompting authorities to implement a "smart lockdown" to curb pollution-causing activities. Despite these efforts, the heavy smog persisted.
title: Pakistan chokes with alarming levels of pollution as AQI crosses 2100

description: The eight bells of Notre Dame Cathedral rang together for the first time since the 2019 fire, marking a significant step in the cathedral's restoration. The bells, housed in the northern belfry, underwent extensive repair and cleaning.
title: Notre Dame's bells ring for first time after 5 years of silence since catastrophic fire

description: Sanju Samson, after his second consecutive T20I century, credited his recent success to captain Suryakumar Yadav's unwavering support and clear communication. Samson revealed that Surya and team management assured him of a consistent opening position for seven matches, boosting his confidence and allowing him to play with freedom.
title: 'Chetta, agla 7 match tera': Surya told Samson

description: India A speedster Prasidh Krishna made a sensational start in the second innings of the India A vs Australia A game, taking two wickets in the first over. He dismissed Marcus Harris and Cameron Bancroft on consecutive deliveries, both for golden ducks, putting Australia A in early trouble in their chase of 169.
title: Watch: Fiery Prasidh grabs two-in-two in first over vs Australia A

description: Over 500 migratory birds have died at Rajasthan's Sambhar Lake since October 26 due to an outbreak of avian botulism.  Rescue teams are working to save sick birds, transporting them to a rescue center in Mithri for treatment. This incident follows a similar outbreak in 2019 that killed approximately 18,000 birds.
title: What is Avian Botulism, that has killed over 500 migratory birds in Rajasthan

description: Eleven security guards in Ahmedabad, India, were caught stealing submersible pumps worth Rs 4 lakh from the industrial unit they were hired to protect. They switched off the power supply and CCTV cameras during the Diwali holidays but were caught on a battery-run camera.
title: Switch off lights, CCTVs for two hours: Factory guards steal pumps in Gujarat

description: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) has cut variable pay for some employees in the July-September quarter due to a challenging demand environment and economic uncertainties. While junior-level employees received their full variable pay, others received reduced amounts or none at all, based on factors like office attendance and business unit performance.
title: TCS cuts variable pay of senior staff for July-September quarter: What the company has to say

description: Abhishek Sharma's recent struggles with the bat have drawn criticism, particularly his aggressive batting approach. Former cricketer Aakash Chopra expressed concerns over Sharma's performance in the first T20I against South Africa, contrasting it with Sanju Samson's century. Chopra highlighted Sharma's declining form since his century and questioned his shot selection.
title: 'Prisoner of his own reputation': Abhishek under fire after another failure

description: Police in Kerala filed a case following an investigation into food kits bearing images of Congress leaders Rahul Gandhi and Priyanka Gandhi, seized ahead of bypolls in Wayanad. The kits, containing staples like rice and sugar, were discovered near a Congress leader's residence. the kits also included pictures of Karnataka chief minister Siddharamaiah, and deputy CM DK Shivakumar, as per PTI sources.
title: Case registered over Rahul, Priyanka Gandhi's images on food kits in Wayanad

description: Tensions escalate in the Middle East as the Israeli Defence Forces (IDF) conduct airstrikes on Hezbollah targets in Tyre, Lebanon, resulting in casualties and significant damage. The strikes, part of an ongoing operation, have drawn condemnation and raised concerns about civilian safety.
title: Watch: Israel intensifies airstrikes on Hezbollah, targets command centers in Lebanon

description: Friday Night SmackDown saw Roman Reigns reunite with the OG Bloodline, but their celebration was cut short by Solo Sikoa's challenge. Sikoa, aligning with Sami Zayn, proposed a WarGames match against Reigns and the Bloodline. In a shocking turn of events, Zayn betrayed Sikoa, siding with the OG Bloodline and leaving Reigns and Zayn standing tall.
title: WWE SmackDown results & highlights 11/08: OG Bloodline, Sami Zayn and more
Blast at Pakistan railway station kills over a dozen, injures 30

description: A 25-year-old Melbourne man, Jacob Hersant, was sentenced to a month in jail for performing the Nazi salute outside a court. This marked the first such sentencing under Victoria's new law banning Nazi symbols. Although briefly jailed, Hersant was later granted bail pending an appeal. The case has ignited debate about free speech and hate crime.
title: Man arrested in Australia for performing Nazi salute, released on bail after an hour

description: Income Tax officials conducted raids on the residences of Sunil Srivastava, the personal secretary of Jharkhand CM Hemant Soren, along with other individuals on Saturday. Reports indicate that approximately nine premises in Ranchi and Jamshedpur are being searched as part of the investigation. Further details on the raids and their purpose are awaited.
title: I-T dept raids Jharkhand CM Hemant Soren's personal secretary's residence in Ranchi

description: A four-year-old girl is in critical condition after a drunk driving accident. The accident occurred on Palm Beach Road and killed the girl's father. The girl's mother sustained minor injuries. The accused driver's father has assured financial aid for the girl's surgery. Citizens are requested to contribute to the hospital bills.
title: Palm Beach Road mishap: 4-year-old girl critical, kin grapple to pay for surgery

description: Indian pilgrims planning to celebrate Guru Nanak Dev's birth anniversary in Pakistan are facing a hurdle. The Pakistan government is urging them to carry US dollars due to a foreign exchange shortage, causing concerns for devotees who may struggle to obtain foreign currency, especially on short notice.
title: 'Bring US dollars instead of Indian currency': Pakistan government urges Sikh pilgrims

description: Jairam Thakur, Leader of the Opposition, criticizes the Himachal Pradesh government, alleging misplaced priorities amidst concerns about law and order and alleged corruption. Thakur highlights a purported CID investigation into refreshments meant for the Chief Minister being served to staff as indicative of these misplaced priorities.
title: Cops probing samosas instead of crime: Jairam Thakur

description: Singham Again has seen a dip in the numbers even on its second Friday and made around Rs 7 crore. The total collection of the movie so far has now crossed Rs 180 crore.
title: ‘Singham Again’ box office collection: Ajay Devgn starrer dips, crosses Rs180 cr

description: The US has urged Qatar to expel Hamas leaders. This follows Hamas's rejection of ceasefire and hostage exchange proposals. Qatar has asked Hamas leaders to leave. Qatar has hosted Hamas leaders since 2012 as part of a negotiation agreement. The US has expressed impatience with Qatar's ties to Hamas. Hamas officials deny receiving a formal request to leave Qatar.
title: Qatar asks Hamas officials to leave country after US pressure: Report

description: During the first T20I match in Durban, tensions flared between Indian captain Suryakumar Yadav and South African pacer Marco Jansen.  The altercation stemmed from Jansen's disapproval of Indian wicketkeeper Sanju Samson collecting a throw on the pitch.  Despite the on-field friction, India secured a commanding victory, defeating South Africa by 61 runs.
title: Watch: SKY, Jansen involved in heated exchange of words

description: India A wicketkeeper-batter Dhruv Jurel continued his impressive form with another crucial half-century (68) in the second unofficial Test against Australia A at the MCG. His knock, along with Nitish Reddy's 38, helped India A recover from a top-order collapse and set Australia A a challenging target of 168 runs.
title: Dhruv Jurel impresses again, slams back-to-back fifties vs Australia A

description: The Malad West constituency is witnessing a fierce political battle.  Congress MLA Aslam Shaikh is seeking re-election. BJP has fielded former corporator Vinod Shelar against him. Shaikh has won three consecutive terms from this constituency. Shelar is highlighting issues like drug proliferation and illegal slums during his campaign. He is confident of winning this election.
title: Maharashtra polls: In Congress's bastion, BJP banks on loyalists, sheds 'outsider' tag

description: Three coaches of the Secunderabad-Shalimar Superfast Express derailed near Nalpur Station, leading to a disruption in rail services. Thankfully, no casualties were reported. This incident follows two other recent derailments in Tamil Nadu and Assam, both of which also resulted in no injuries but caused service delays.
title: Three coaches of Secunderabad-Shalimar Express derail near Howrah

description: The Board of Control for Cricket in India has informed the Pakistan Cricket Board that India is unlikely to travel to Pakistan for the ICC Champions Trophy. The BCCI, awaiting government clearance, prefers to play its matches in Dubai. PCB chief Mohsin Naqvi denies receiving formal communication, while the ICC's decision on the tournament's schedule is pending.
title: BCCI wants India's CT matches in Dubai? No such request yet: PCB

description: The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) held a meeting to discuss the Indian cricket team's recent Test series loss against New Zealand. The meeting involved key figures such as the BCCI secretary, team captain, head coach, and chief selector. The team's strategy for the upcoming Border-Gavaskar series in Australia was also analyzed.
title: BCCI holds six-hour review meeting after New Zealand whitewash

description: Sanju Samson's stellar form continues as he smashed his second consecutive T20I century, leading India to a resounding victory against South Africa. Samson emphasized his aggressive approach and intent for boundary hitting. Captain Suryakumar Yadav also praised Samson's dedication and hard work, highlighting his commitment to the team's success.
title: Samson trying to make 'maximum' utilisation of current form

description: Sanju Samson etched his name in the record books, becoming the first Indian batter to score consecutive T20I centuries. His blistering 107 off 50 balls powered India to a commanding 61-run victory against South Africa in the series opener at Kingsmead, Durban. Samson's innings, studded with seven fours and ten sixes was hailed by social media.
title: 'Permanent opener till 2026 WC': Fans laud Samson ton

description: Zimbabwe's government announced a new regulation requiring WhatsApp group administrators to register with POTRAZ and obtain a license costing at least $50. The regulation aims to curb misinformation and align with the Data Protection Act.
title: WhatsApp users in this country will need to pay licence fee to postal department to become WhatsApp Group admins

description: Shiv Sena (UBT) leader Uddhav Thackeray criticized UP CM Yogi Adityanath's recent political slogan. Thackeray questioned the unity of the Mahayuti alliance. He also accused the BJP of using the Shiv Sena for political gains. Thackeray apologized for trusting the breakaway Shiv Sena faction. He called them 'dacoits' for stealing the party's name and symbol.
title: Uddhav slams Yogi for ‘batenge toh katenge’ remark, says Maha lives in 'harmony'

description: Elon Musk joined Donald Trump's congratulatory call with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, assuring continued Starlink support for Ukraine. This marked Trump's first post-election contact with Zelenskyy, who found the call encouraging. Musk's presence highlights his growing influence, following his substantial campaign contribution to Trump and speculation about a potential cabinet position.
title: Elon Musk joins Donald Trump on his 25-minute phone call with Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy, and why it matters

description: Three men were arrested in Noida for the murder of a 20-year-old man named Ashu. The accused, seeking revenge for an earlier altercation over a loan repayment, stabbed Ashu multiple times. Ashu's friend, Vishal, was also injured while trying to intervene. Police have recovered the murder weapons and are searching for a fourth suspect.
title: Rs 3,000 loan, a ‘slap’ & spat: Trio stab man repeatedly, arrested in Noida

description: Maharashtra's Assembly elections highlight a stark gender imbalance, with only 10% of candidates being women.  A mere 97 constituencies out of 288 lack a single female contender, despite both major political alliances advocating for women's empowerment.  While the delayed women's reservation bill is blamed, critics emphasize the need for parties to prioritize qualified women beyond just family members.
title: Maharashtra polls: Not even 1 woman candidate in 97 assembly seats

description: Singaporean government officials, including minister K Shanmugam, met with Tata Group chairman N Chandrasekaran to discuss a semiconductor partnership. Singapore, a major player in the semiconductor industry, aims to collaborate with Tata Group's extensive reach.  The discussions also included skills development, digital initiatives, industrial parks, and renewable energy.
title: Tatas, Singapore government in talks to develop semiconductors

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during his Maharashtra campaign trail, accused Congress of employing divisive tactics to secure political advantage. He alleged that Congress aims to weaken India by inciting discord among Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes, and OBCs. Modi emphasized the importance of unity, stating that a united India is a secure India.
title: In Dhule, LS seat that BJP lost, PM delivers ‘Ek hain...’ message

description: Two MBBS students died in a late-night sports bike crash in Bhopal, raising concerns about youth speeding on city roads. Police acknowledge the issue but cite difficulties in strict monitoring due to highways connecting districts and the focus on theft prevention at night.
title: Killer speed, stunts & reels: Rash driving a scary ‘trend’ in Bhopal

description: A Hindi teacher at a Bengaluru private school allegedly broke a sixth-grader's tooth for splashing water on her. The boy's father claims the teacher struck his son with a wooden roll, while the school administration insists the injury occurred accidentally while the boy was trying to escape punishment. Police are investigating the incident.
title: Bengaluru teacher 'breaks' student’s tooth over spilled water on her clothes
